X_1, \ldots, X_k
\mathcal D
Y = \frac{X_1 + \cdots + X_{k-1}}{k-1}
X_k
 \mathbf E \left[\frac{1}{k} \sum_{i=1}^k \left| X_i - \frac{X_1 + X_2 + \cdots + X_k}{k} \right| \right] 
 \begin{align*} \mathbf E \left[\left| X_k - \frac{X_1 + X_2 + \cdots + X_k}{k} \right| \right]  &=  \mathbf E \left[\left| \frac{(k-1)X_k - (X_1 + X_2 + \cdots + X_{k-1})}{k} \right| \right]  \\ &= \frac{k-1}{k} \cdot \mathbf E \left[\left| X_k - \frac{X_1 + X_2 + \cdots + X_{k-1}}{k-1} \right| \right]  \\ &= \frac{k-1}{k} \cdot \mathbf E \left[\left| X_k - Y \right| \right]  \end{align*} 
